# Passive Component Sizing Strategy

## Context

Reference design for QFN48 uses 0201 components extensively.

Concern: manufacturability during hand assembly.

## Strategy

Divide components into categories:

### RF-Critical (retain 0201)
- Matching network (L1, L2, C3, C4)
- RF path components

### Timing-Critical
- Crystal load capacitors (Considering move to 0402 with tight placement)

### General Passives
- Decoupling capacitors
- Pull-ups / resistors

→ Standardized to 0402 where possible

### Bulk Components
- Larger capacitors (1 µF) allowed in 0603

## Rationale

- Maintain RF integrity
- Improve assembly success rate
- Reduce placement difficulty

## Notes

Component size affects parasitics at RF frequencies. Changes are acceptable outside RF path if layout remains tight.